items.name: Women-Safety-and-Analytics
items.description: The Real-Time Surveillance and Analytical Solution is designed to enhance public safety, with a particular focus on protecting women from potential threats. The system integrates advanced video analytics, machine learning, and real-time monitoring to create a proactive and responsive safety framework.

items.name: ACON
items.description: A dynamic and adaptive machine learning framework designed for maximum optimization and adaptability across diverse datasets and environments. This is an open-source project, so please, feel free to share improvements/comments/suggestions

items.name: MachineLearningImageRecognation
items.description: In this project, you will learn how to integrate CoreML into a Swift application. CoreML is a framework that enables the use of machine learning models in Apple platforms. We utilize the MobileNetV2 model for image classification. Additionally, this project highlights the differences between DispatchQueue.main.async and DispatchQueue.global.

items.name: MLonBAO
items.description: Framework for Impact Analysis of Contention on Multi-Core Platforms for Real-Time Critical Applications and Machine Learning

items.name: Planter
items.description: Planter is a modular framework for realising in one-click in-network machine learning algorithms.

items.name: Interactive-ML-Model-Deployment-with-GUI
items.description: This project focuses on embedding machine learning models into an interactive, user-friendly application using Streamlit, enabling third-party stakeholders to make real-time predictions without technical knowledge. The project follows the final step of the CRISP-DM frameworkâ€”deployment, ensuring the model is accessible for practical decision-making

items.name: UNVEILING-THE-LUNG-CANCER-ENIGMA-A-MULTI-AGENT-SYSTEMS-ML-FOR-PRECISION-PREDICTION-AND-ANALYSIS
items.description: Unraveling the complexities of lung cancer through a groundbreaking multi-agent systems framework. Our project leverages machine learning for precision prediction and analysis, offering a novel approach to combat this deadly disease.

items.name: porter
items.description: porter is a framework for exposing machine learning models via REST APIs.

items.name: Flower-AWS-FederatedLearning
items.description: An implementation of federated learning using the Flower framework on AWS. It enables distributed machine learning across multiple devices while preserving data privacy. The system leverages AWS services for scalable and secure deployment.
